-- Hong Kong Democrat Leader Albert Ho to Resign on Election Result
-- B y   S i m o n   L e e
-- 2012-09-10T02:39:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-10/hong-kong-democrat-leader-albert-ho-to-resign-on-election-result.html
Hong Kong Democratic Party Chairman
Albert Ho will resign as leader after his party lost seats in
the legislative elections.  Ho “accepts responsibility” for the election result and
said the party lost out to more aggressive groups.  The party won 4 out of 35 seats that are elected by
geographical constituencies.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Simon Lee in Hong Kong at 
